                    <ab>In n(omine) D(omi)ni. Constat me <persName key="#Priests"><name ref="Petrus"
                                >Petrus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">p(res)b(ite)r</rs> Pitulo <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1498" key="#Churches">s(an)c(t)e Cumioclensis
                            Eccl(esi)e</orgName>, iubente(a) d(omi)no meo <persName key="#Bishops"
                            ref="#people/1571">Ioh(anne)s</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">ep(iscopu)s</rs> s(uprascrip)te s(an)c(t)e
                        Cumiacl(e)ns(i)s Eccl(esi)e, accepisse et accepi a vob(is) <persName
                            key="#Priests"><name ref="Albinus">Albinus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">p(res)b(ite)r</rs> pen(sionem) de una <rs key="#Houses"
                            >mansione</rs> cu(m) <rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs> iuxta se habente q(ui)
                        e(st) p(o)s(ita) in <placeName ref="#places/485">Cumiaclo</placeName>, in
                        regione <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/1481">S(an)c(t)e Marie q(ui)
                            v(o)c(atur) Fermosa</orgName>, que(m) p(er) <rs
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis">enfiteusin</rs> tenere viso estis
                        ad iura n(ost)ra eccl(esi)a, om(n)iq(ue) ann(o) in festivitate s(an)c(t)i
                        Cassiani p(e)n(sionem) <rs key="#Rent_in_money">d(e)n(ariorum) tres</rs>
                        t(an)t(um). Unde p(ro) munimine v(est)ro feci vob(is) hoc deaccepto in
                        m(en)se aug(usto), indic(tione) s(e)c(un)da, Cumiaclo.</ab>
                </div>
